John Cage (1912)
studied with Richard Buhlig, Adolph Weiss, Henry Cowell, and Arnold Schoenberg
percussion ensembles @ Cornish School in Seattle (1936-1938)
directed concert of percussion music (1943)
	sponsored by the Museum of Modern Art and the Leagues of Composers.

invented "prepared piano" (1938)
1951: musicians and engineers gathered to record on magnetic tape


